    Abstract base class to simplify implementing an Iterator for concrete subclasses of AbstractHugeHashSet.

    The mutating operation is implemented as a protected method with the suffix "Internal".

      • removeInternal

        protected void removeInternal()
        Removes the last retrieved element from the underlying collection.

        This method has the same semantics as Iterator.remove(). Mutable subclasses can implement Iterator.remove() by calling this method.

        Immutable subclasses can call this method from the builder.
